{
  "texts": [
    "To mitigate these limitations, graph neural networks (GNN) have more sophisticated encoders that take advantage of the structure, features, and attributes of graphs [112].Su et al. [113] proposed constrained multi-view nonnegative matrix factorization (CMNMF), a model based on GNN, to determine the similarity between drugs and viruses within their space of characteristics (latent space).",
    "Therefore, CMNMF is oriented towards preserving drug and virus similarity information as much as possible.",
    "Then, they apply a graph convolutional network (GCN) with attention-based neighbor sampling to optimize the vectorial representation of drugs and viruses in virus-drug associations (VDA) networks, whereas VDA networks are considered heterogeneous graphs.",
    "The experiments were executed on three VDA datasets to identify possible drugs against SARS-CoV-2.",
    "The embedding algorithm from Su et al."
  ]
}